#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:0.5"
msgid "4. Purāṇacīvarasikkhāpada"
msgstr "4. The training rule on used robes"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-np4.1, pts-vp-en2.30, ms1V_1941
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato udāyissa purāṇadutiyikā bhikkhunīsu pabbajitā hoti."
msgstr "At that time Venerable Udāyī’s former wife had become a nun."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.3"
msgid "Sā āyasmato udāyissa santike abhikkhaṇaṃ āgacchati."
msgstr "She frequently visited Udāyī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.4"
msgid "Āyasmāpi udāyī tassā bhikkhuniyā santike abhikkhaṇaṃ gacchati."
msgstr "and he frequently visited her."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.5"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udāyī tassā bhikkhuniyā santike bhattavissaggaṃ karoti."
msgstr "And Udāyī shared his meals with that nun."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, pts-vp-pli3.206, ms1V_1942
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.6"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā udāyī pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena sā bhikkhunī tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "One morning Udāyī robed up, took his bowl and robe, and went to her."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.7"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā tassā bhikkhuniyā purato aṅgajātaṃ vivaritvā āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "He then uncovered his genitals in front of her and sat down on a seat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.8"
msgid "Sāpi kho bhikkhunī āyasmato udāyissa purato aṅgajātaṃ vivaritvā āsane nisīdi."
msgstr "She too uncovered her genitals in front of him and sat down on a seat."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.9"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā udāyī sāratto tassā bhikkhuniyā aṅgajātaṃ upanijjhāyi."
msgstr "Udāyī lustfully stared at her genitals,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.10"
msgid "Tassa asuci mucci."
msgstr "and he emitted semen."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.11"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā udāyī taṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "He then said to that nun:"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.12"
msgid "“gaccha, bhagini, udakaṃ āhara,"
msgstr "“Sister, get some water;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.13"
msgid "antaravāsakaṃ dhovissāmī”ti."
msgstr "I’ll wash the robe.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.14"
msgid "“Āharayya, ahameva dhovissāmī”ti"
msgstr "“Give it to me, Venerable, I’ll wash it.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.15"
msgid "taṃ asuciṃ ekadesaṃ mukhena aggahesi ekadesaṃ aṅgajāte pakkhipi."
msgstr "She then took some of the semen in her mouth and inserted some into her genitals."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.16"
msgid "Sā tena gabbhaṃ gaṇhi."
msgstr "Because of that she became pregnant."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.17"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo evamāhaṃsu—"
msgstr "The nuns said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.18"
msgid "“abrahmacārinī ayaṃ bhikkhunī,"
msgstr "“This nun is not abstaining from sexuality;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.19"
msgid "gabbhinī”ti."
msgstr "she’s pregnant.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.20"
msgid "“Nāhaṃ, ayye, abrahmacārinī”ti bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi."
msgstr "She said, “Venerables, I do abstain from sexuality,” and she told them what had happened."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-en2.31
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.21"
msgid "Bhikkhuniyo ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "The nuns complained and criticized Udāyī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.22"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma ayyo udāyī bhikkhuniyā purāṇacīvaraṃ dhovāpessatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Udāyī get a nun to wash a used robe?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.23"
msgid "Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They then told the monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.24"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.25"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.26"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma āyasmā udāyī bhikkhuniyā purāṇacīvaraṃ dhovāpessatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Udāyī get a nun to wash a used robe?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, ms1V_1943
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.27"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing him in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.28"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, udāyi, bhikkhuniyā purāṇacīvaraṃ dhovāpesī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Udāyī, that you did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.29"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.30"
msgid "“Ñātikā te, udāyi, aññātikā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is she a relative of yours?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.31"
msgid "“Aññātikā, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“No, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.32"
msgid "“Aññātako, moghapurisa, aññātikāya na jānāti patirūpaṃ vā appatirūpaṃ vā pāsādikaṃ vā apāsādikaṃ vā."
msgstr "“Foolish man, a man and a woman who are not related don’t know what’s appropriate and what’s inappropriate in dealing with each other, what’s inspiring behavior and what’s not."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.33"
msgid "Tattha nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā purāṇacīvaraṃ dhovāpessasi."
msgstr "And still you got an unrelated nun to wash a used robe."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.34"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.35"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.35a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc4, ms1V_1944
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:1.36"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā purāṇacīvaraṃ dhovāpeyya vā rajāpeyya vā ākoṭāpeyya vā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk gets an unrelated nun to wash, dye, or beat a used robe, he commits and offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc5, pts-cs-bu-np4.2.1, ms1V_1945
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. HTML: </span><span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, ms1V_1946
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.6"
msgid "Aññātikā nāma"
msgstr "Unrelated:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.7"
msgid "mātito vā pitito vā yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā asambaddhā."
msgstr "anyone who is not a descendant of one’s male ancestors going back seven generations, either on the mother’s side or on the father’s side."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, pts-vp-en2.32, ms1V_1947
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.8"
msgid "Bhikkhunī nāma"
msgstr "A nun:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.9"
msgid "ubhatosaṃghe upasampannā."
msgstr "she has been given the full ordination by both Orders."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, ms1V_1948
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.10"
msgid "Purāṇacīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "A used robe:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.11"
msgid "sakiṃ nivatthampi sakiṃ pārutampi."
msgstr "a lower robe or an upper robe, even worn once."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.12"
msgid "Dhovāti āṇāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he tells her to wash it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.13"
msgid "Dhotaṃ nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When it has been washed, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.14"
msgid "Rajāti āṇāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he tells her to dye it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.15"
msgid "Rattaṃ nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When it has been died, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.16"
msgid "Ākoṭehīti āṇāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he tells her to beat it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.17"
msgid "Sakiṃ pāṇippahāraṃ vā muggarappahāraṃ vā dinne nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When she has struck it once with her hand or with an implement, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.18"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The robe should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. HTML: <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.19"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. HTML: <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.20"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "To be expanded as in [Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17](pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#23-#29), with appropriate substitutions. "

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.21"
msgid "idaṃ me, bhante, purāṇacīvaraṃ aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā dhovāpitaṃ nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘Venerables, this used robe which I got an unrelated nun to wash is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.22"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmīti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.23"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.24"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.1.25"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this robe back to you.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc10, pts-vp-pli3.207, pts-cs-bu-np4.2.2, ms1V_1950, pts-vp-en2.33
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.1"
msgid "Aññātikāya aññātikasaññī purāṇacīvaraṃ dhovāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If she is unrelated and he perceives her as unrelated, and he gets her to wash a used robe, he commits one offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.2"
msgid "Aññātikāya aññātikasaññī purāṇacīvaraṃ dhovāpeti rajāpeti, nissaggiyena āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If she is unrelated and he perceives her as unrelated, and he gets her to wash and dye a used robe, he commits one offense entailing relinquishment and one offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.3"
msgid "Aññātikāya aññātikasaññī purāṇacīvaraṃ dhovāpeti ākoṭāpeti, nissaggiyena āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If she is unrelated and he perceives her as unrelated, and he gets her to wash and beat a used robe, he commits one offense entailing relinquishment and one offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.4"
msgid "Aññātikāya aññātikasaññī purāṇacīvaraṃ dhovāpeti rajāpeti ākoṭāpeti, nissaggiyena āpatti dvinnaṃ dukkaṭānaṃ."
msgstr "If she is unrelated and he perceives her as unrelated, and he gets her to wash, dye, and beat a used robe, he commits one offense entailing relinquishment and two offenses of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11, ms1V_1951
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.5"
msgid "Aññātikāya aññātikasaññī purāṇacīvaraṃ rajāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If she is unrelated and he perceives her as unrelated, and he gets her to dye a used robe, he commits one offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.6"
msgid "Aññātikāya aññātikasaññī purāṇacīvaraṃ rajāpeti ākoṭāpeti, nissaggiyena āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If she is unrelated and he perceives her as unrelated, and he gets her to dye and beat a used robe, he commits one offense entailing relinquishment and one offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.7"
msgid "Aññātikāya aññātikasaññī purāṇacīvaraṃ rajāpeti dhovāpeti, nissaggiyena āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If she is unrelated and he perceives her as unrelated, and he gets her to dye and wash a used robe, he commits one offense entailing relinquishment and one offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.8"
msgid "Aññātikāya aññātikasaññī purāṇacīvaraṃ rajāpeti ākoṭāpeti dhovāpeti, nissaggiyena āpatti dvinnaṃ dukkaṭānaṃ."
msgstr "If she is unrelated and he perceives her as unrelated, and he gets her to dye, beat, and wash a used robe, he commits one offense entailing relinquishment and two offenses of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms1V_1952
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.9"
msgid "Aññātikāya aññātikasaññī purāṇacīvaraṃ ākoṭāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If she is unrelated and he perceives her as unrelated, and he gets her to beat a used robe, he commits one offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.10"
msgid "Aññātikāya aññātikasaññī purāṇacīvaraṃ ākoṭāpeti dhovāpeti, nissaggiyena āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If she is unrelated and he perceives her as unrelated, and he gets her to beat and wash a used robe, he commits one offense entailing relinquishment and one offense of wrong conduct."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.34
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.11"
msgid "Aññātikāya aññātikasaññī purāṇacīvaraṃ ākoṭāpeti rajāpeti, nissaggiyena āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If she is unrelated and he perceives her as unrelated, and he gets her to beat and dye a used robe, he commits one offense entailing relinquishment and one offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.12"
msgid "Aññātikāya aññātikasaññī purāṇacīvaraṃ ākoṭāpeti dhovāpeti rajāpeti, nissaggiyena āpatti dvinnaṃ dukkaṭānaṃ."
msgstr "If she is unrelated and he perceives her as unrelated, and he gets her to beat, wash, and dye a used robe, he commits one offense entailing relinquishment and two offenses of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13, ms1V_1953
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.13"
msgid "Aññātikāya vematiko … pe …"
msgstr "If she is unrelated, but he is unsure if she is …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.14"
msgid "aññātikāya ñātikasaññī … pe …"
msgstr "If she is unrelated, but he perceives her as related …"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.15"
msgid "aññassa purāṇacīvaraṃ dhovāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he gets her to wash a used robe belonging to someone else, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.16"
msgid "Nisīdanapaccattharaṇaṃ dhovāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he gets her to wash a sitting-mat or a bed sheet, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.17"
msgid "Ekatoupasampannāya dhovāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he gets a nun who is fully ordained only on one side to do the washing, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.18"
msgid "Ñātikāya aññātikasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If she is related, but he perceives her as unrelated, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.19"
msgid "Ñātikāya vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If she is related, but he is unsure if she is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.20"
msgid "Ñātikāya ñātikasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If she is related and he perceives her as related, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.20a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.21"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.22"
msgid "ñātikāya dhovantiyā aññātikā dutiyā hoti,"
msgstr "if a related nun does the washing and an unrelated nun helps her;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.23"
msgid "avuttā dhovati,"
msgstr "if a nun does the washing without being asked;"

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.35
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.24"
msgid "aparibhuttaṃ dhovāpeti,"
msgstr "if he gets a nun to wash an unused robe;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.25"
msgid "cīvaraṃ ṭhapetvā aññaṃ parikkhāraṃ dhovāpeti,"
msgstr "if he gets a nun to wash any requisite apart from a robe;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.26"
msgid "sikkhamānāya,"
msgstr "if it is a trainee nun;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.27"
msgid "sāmaṇeriyā,"
msgstr "if it is a novice nun;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.28"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.29"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc15, ms1V_1955
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np4:2.2.30"
msgid "Purāṇacīvarasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ."
msgstr "The fourth rule, the training rule on used robes, is finished."
